SIMPLE: height
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Height
<hw>Height</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hight</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[OE. <ets>heighte</ets>,
<ets>heght</ets>, <ets>heighthe</ets>, AS. <ets>he⟦aacute⟧h⟦edh⟧u</ets>,
<ets>h⟦emac⟧h⟦edh⟧u</ets> fr. <ets>heah</ets> high; akin to D.
<ets>hoogte</ets>, Sw. <ets>h⟦oum⟧jd</ets>, Dan. <ets>h⟦oum⟧ide</ets>,
Icel. <ets>h⟦ae⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>, Goth. <ets>hauhi⟦thorn⟧a</ets>. See
<er>High</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of being high;
elevated position.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold the <qex>height</qex> of the stars, how high they are!</q>
<rj><qau>Job xxii. 12.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The distance to which anything rises above its foot,
above that on which in stands, above the earth, or above the level of
the sea; altitude; the measure upward from a surface, as the floor or
the ground, of an animal, especially of a man; stature.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Goliath's] <qex>height</qex> was six cubits and a span.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Sam. xvii. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Degree of latitude either north or south.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Guinea lieth to the north sea, in the same <qex>height</qex> as
Peru to the south.</q> <rj><qau>Abp. Abbot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>That which is elevated; an eminence; a hill or
mountain; <as>as, Alpine <ex>heights</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Elevation in excellence of any kind, as in power,
learning, arts; also, an advanced degree of social rank; pre⟦eum⟧minence
or distinction in society; prominence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Measure your mind's <qex>height</qex> by the shade it casts.</q>
<rj><qau>R. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All would in his power hold, all make his subjects.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Progress toward eminence; grade; degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Social duties are carried to greater <qex>heights</qex>, and
enforced with stronger motives by the principles of our religion.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Utmost degree in extent; extreme limit of energy or
condition; <as>as, the <ex>height</ex> of a fever, of passion, of
madness, of folly; the <ex>height</ex> of a tempest.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My grief was at the <qex>height</qex> before thou camest.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>On height</b></col>, <cd>aloud.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] spake these same words, all <qex>on hight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Heighten</ent>⟦br⟧
